By the time a buyer books a demo with you, the decision is mostly made. And it wasn't made on your website.

The B2B buying journey stopped being a funnel a while ago. It looks more like a web. Before a prospect ever fills out a form, they have already:

→ Read a few G2 reviews
→ Lurked a Reddit, Inc. thread comparing you to two competitors
→ Watched a YouTube teardown of your SaaS
→ Asked ChatGPT and Claude to both give a point of view on who the best options are

Most of that happens in places your brand does not control, and it shapes the shortlist whether the buyer notices or not… 

The stages where someone decides who makes the cut have moved onto third-party turf. Reddit, review sites, independent communities. 

Those are the same sources the AI models pull from when they build answers. 

Reddit is one of the most cited domains in AI Overviews and ChatGPT responses today. 

Skip those conversations and the models have no reason to mention you when a buyer asks for recommendations.

Here’s what our team at Foundation Marketing has done about it for billion-dollar brands influencing B2B buyers in Martech, Payroll, HR, Cybersecurity, Sales & more:

→ Stood up real Reddit presences:
Create both user accounts and subreddits. These aren’t bot accounts. It’s not executing astroturf campaigns. We create accounts for our clients that are transparently theirs and that answer questions and earn trust in the subreddits where the category gets argued over.

→ Optimized 150+ old YouTube videos:
Most brands treat their YouTube channel like a bookshelf collecting old webinars and clips. The reality is that inside of that collection is content gold for both LLMs and buying decisions. 

→ Used reviews to drive product change: 
Most brands treat negative reviews as a reputation management problem. In most cases, these are actually customer support or fundamental product issues. We surface these insights not just to understand LLMs & training data BUT ALSO to arm product teams with insights to build a better product & customer service roadmap. 

→ Hired niche YouTubers to create BOFU content
YouTube dominates the SERP and is slowly showing up in more LLMs. We’ve created YouTube strategies on the back of influencer marketing that has helped our clients own the category and the SERP with high intent content. 

And so much more. 

With the B2B Journey looking this different. 

Marketing teams need to act different. 

Remember:

None of this lands if your own house is a mess:

→ Create a product / offering worth using 
→ Understand the pains of your customers
→ Monitor the right prompts and keywords 
→ Answer questions instead of burying them
→ Make the content easy to quote and cite
→ Give the model a clean reason to pull from you

For CMOs, start here…

1. Map where your category actually gets discussed and decided
2. Show up there like a human who knows things
3. Make your owned pages and off-site content ready to answer the question for a person and for an AI

The buying journey did not get more complicated. 

Trust just moved to rooms you do not own….

The brands winning right now are the ones showing up in those rooms anyway.

